Attribution
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Psylli's Razer HID protocol implementation is derived from OpenRazer:

    OpenRazer — https://github.com/openrazer/openrazer
    Licensed under the GNU General Public License v2.0.

Specifically, the report structure, CRC, transaction IDs, command classes, and
Chroma matrix-effect encodings in the `razer-proto` crate are a port of, and are
validated byte-for-byte against, the following OpenRazer sources:

    driver/razercommon.c
    driver/razercommon.h
    driver/razerchromacommon.c
    driver/razermouse_driver.c

OpenRazer is the work of its many contributors and performed the original
reverse-engineering of Razer's USB HID control protocol. Psylli would not exist
without it. This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by the OpenRazer
project.

